<section xml:id="materials" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
	<title>Class Materials</title>
	<subsection xml:id="subsec-textbook">
		<title>Textbook</title>
		<p>
			For this class we will be using <pubtitle>APEX Calculus, 4th Edition</pubtitle>. 
				This course will cover material from chapters 1-4. Some releases of the text are divided into quarters; in that case, we are using the Q1 section.
		</p>
		<p>
				There are multiple releases available:
			<ul>
				<li><url href = "https://spot.pcc.edu/math/APEXCalculus/">eText</url>for web viewing,</li>
				<li><url href = "https://www.openintro.org/go?id=apex4-q1-color">Color PDF</url> for reading on a screen,</li>
				<li><url href = "https://www.openintro.org/go?id=apex4-q1-bw">Black and White PDF</url> for black-ink printing, and</li>
				<li><url href = "https://www.amazon.com/dp/172297317X/">Paperback</url> for purchase on Amazon.</li>
			</ul>
			You can find more information at <url href="https://apexcalculus.com"/>.
		</p>
	</subsection>
	<subsection xml:id="subsec-technology">
		<title>Technology</title>
		<p>
			<ul>
				<li>Personal computer, webcam, microphone, and internet access required for attending lectures.</li>
				<li>Graphing technology is required. Desmos and/or Geogebra are options available at no cost.</li>
				<li>All courses are web-enchanced and all students are required to have access to CANVAS which can be 
					accessed through the main <url href="OregonCoast.edu">OCCC Website</url>. All faculty must use 
				the CANVAS gradebook so that students can easily track their grades.</li>
			</ul>
		</p>
	</subsection>
</section>
